The paper deals with exact algorithms for the maximum clique problem, which is a well-known problem in computer science and graph theory. The focus is on computational study and analysis of program code, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) or Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. However, the use of algorithms and analysis of their behavior on different hardware platforms suggests that the paper may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) or Computational Complexity (cs.CC) sub-categories. Finally, the investigation of vertex ordering and the effect of rescaling published results suggests that the paper may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
